---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MoonStar from '../../components/decor/MoonStar.astro';
import Sparkles from '../../components/decor/Sparkles.astro';
import ReplyInThread from '../../components/ReplyInThread/ReplyInThread';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Reply in Thread · micro-guide"
  description="A 60-second click-through for Slack and Teams that teaches one habit: reply in the thread, don't start a new message. Plus a reminder GIF you can post in any channel."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-paper paper-bg">
    <MoonStar class="absolute top-10 left-6 sm:left-12 w-10 sm:w-14 h-auto opacity-90 hidden sm:block" />
    <Sparkles class="hidden md:block absolute bottom-8 right-10 w-28 lg:w-36 h-auto opacity-80 pointer-events-none" />
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <p class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-cocoa/50 mb-3">Micro-guide · adoption nudge</p>
      <h1 class="font-display font-semibold text-cocoa text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-tight tracking-tight">
        Reply in the thread. <span class="italic text-primary-600">Not a new message.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-cocoa/75 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        The most common channel-hygiene problem at every company, and a 60-second fix once people see what a stray
        message does to a channel. Built two ways: a click-through for Slack and Teams, and a drop-in GIF for the
        channel where the reminder keeps not sticking.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- Click-through -->
  <section class="bg-cream-50 py-12 sm:py-16 border-t border-cocoa/10">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <p class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-cocoa/50 mb-4">Option 1 · the click-through</p>
      <ReplyInThread client:load />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reminder GIF -->
  <section id="reminder-gif" class="bg-paper border-t border-cocoa/10 py-14 sm:py-16 scroll-mt-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <p class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-cocoa/50 mb-4">Option 2 · the postable reminder</p>
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-cocoa/15 bg-cream-50 p-4 flex items-center justify-center">
          <img
            src="/reminders/reply-in-thread.gif"
            alt="Animated reminder: a question gets buried under new messages, versus a tidy threaded reply that keeps the channel clean."
            class="rounded-xl w-full max-w-md shadow-lg"
            width="640"
            height="420"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-cocoa text-2xl sm:text-3xl leading-tight">
            Drop it in the channel that needs it.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-cocoa/75 leading-relaxed">
            Same lesson, no clicks. A six-second loop: the question gets buried under new messages, then the calm
            version where the answer lives in a thread. Post it once when a channel gets noisy and it does the
            nudging, so you don't have to be the thread police.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a
              href="/reminders/reply-in-thread.gif"
              download
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-full bg-primary-500 text-cream font-semibold retro-sheen hover:bg-primary-600 transition-colors"
            >
              Download the GIF
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v12m0 0l-4-4m4 4l4-4M4 20h16" />
              </svg>
            </a>
            <a
              href="/resources/xapi-in-plain-english"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-full border border-cocoa/25 text-cocoa font-semibold hover:border-primary-500 hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors"
            >
              Why micro-nudges beat all-hands emails
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-cocoa/50">
            Built as a teaching pattern: the same content works as practice (the click-through) or a reminder (the
            GIF). Drop in your own channel names and brand colors and it's yours.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
